[ ] graphd owns portable query families and output formats $Establish graphd as the direct public read/query/export tool. Standard .sparql files opt into index, tree, or graph consumer contracts by family directory; graphd validates and serializes them, while raw/named SPARQL stays unrestricted. The clearhead CLI remains a mutation and workspace-lifecycle convenience and should not forward, decode, or implement graph queries. Neovim and other clients call graphd directly for reads and clearhead for identity-addressed writes. Index output is proven; complete the direct-client cutover before implementing tree/work-map and graph/dependencies showcases.$ !2 #019f76ca-f3b1-7613-a0de-74f453f8576c
    >[ ] implement the graph query family with dependencies $Add queries/graph discovery and standard CONSTRUCT execution. Use dependencies.sparql as the proving query over action identity, labels, states, charter membership, and predecessor edges; emit JSON-LD plus an explicit standard RDF format and a terminal summary, and prove the .sparql/result round-trip through external RDF tooling.$ <019f8b8a-840e-78b0-af82-938b90d7a9ce #019f8b8a-b7fc-7e03-a507-2e47b88f4740
